Description: Small fragment of a seal-impression made of fine brown Nile clay that was hardened after excavation. The rear shows a concave side with impressions of wood like from a bolt. Perpendicular to it the impression of a turned cord with a width of 0.15 cm. The front side is convex and is covered in finger impressions. It shows a small part of a scarab-like seal impression, the signs are not well recognisable. A curved double line at the left, in the middle a vertical line, unrecognisable smaller signs in between, maybe a mn among them.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Amara West (Nubia), E14.7 temple magazine
Acquisition notes: Formerly housed by the Birmingham Museum and Art Gallery and the EES London.
